However, the quality differences between filters are huge. If you have an expensive lens, you do not want to run the risk of image quality losses due to inferior filters. Rodenstock guarantees the best possible filter quality. Optical glass for filters must meet very stringent demands. The glass must be homogeneous, and both surfaces must be “plan parallel”. The surfaces must be smooth. The polish must be equal to that of the surfaces of camera lens elements. The filter frame may not project too far beyond the front edge of the lens barrel so that the filter does not cause vignetting with wide-angle shots. All Rodenstock filters have a very flat slim line frame. In order to allow a front thread, the Rodenstock glass is only 1.4mm thick, compared to other filters are 2.0mm thick or thicker. The frames of the Rodenstock Digital Pro filters are made of aluminum because these filters were designed for the best possible price/performance ratio. The edges of all Rodenstock filter Lenses are blackened so that no contrast-reducing reflections are caused there. If you need more than the ND 2x, 4x and 8x, or want finer graduations, the variable neutral density filter Rodenstock Digital Pro Vario ND. It consists of two polarization filters continuously adjustable from 1.5 to 5 stops. Color neutrality is gradually lost above 5 f-stops. Furthermore, with very wide-angle lenses, disturbing cruciform shading occurs close to the maximum position. Because these very high settings cannot be recommended, the setting scale of the Rodenstock Digital Vario ND only indicates the sensible attenuation range +1.5 to +5: without cruciform shading and without a blue-violet color tinge. NFlightcam Propeller Filter for Smartphones ['Our clip-on propeller filter fits a wide range of smartphones, even without removing the smartphone from its case. Designed for use INSIDE the aircraft only, this filter removes the propeller in 90% of the conditions encountered on a typical VFR flight. HOW IT WORKS: Smartphone image sensors are controlled by the amount of light they sense. In normal lighting conditions, the sensor runs faster than the propeller, causing distortion and odd lines in your video. Our filter modulates the amount of light entering the sensor and keeps the speed of the sensor slower than the propeller. Since the amount of light changes constantly and the filter does not, we designed the filter to completely remove the propeller in 90% of the conditions experienced in VFR flight. For best results, we recommend avoiding shots straight into the sun. SET UP: \ufeffClip the filter over your smartphone camera lens. Check the image on your smartphone screen to ensure the edges of the filter are not in the image. If so, readjust the clip. AS A KIT: If you are interested in buying the entire Smartphone Cockpit Kit instead, it includes this filter, a smartphone audio recording cable, and a suction cup mount for use inside the aircraft only. Perfect-Surface Silver (PSS) is AudioQuest\'s highest-quality metal. Solid conductors prevent strand interaction, a major source of cable distortion. Extremely high-purity Perfect-Surface Silver minimizes distortion caused by the grain boundaries that exist within any metal conductor, nearly eliminating harshness and greatly increasing clarity compared to OFHC, OCC, 8N and other coppers. CARBON-BASED 3-LAYER NOISE- SYSTEM (NDS) It\'s easy to accomplish 100% shield coverage. Preventing captured Radio Frequency Interference (RFI) from modulating the equipment\'s ground reference requires AQ\'s Noise-Dissipation System (NDS). Traditional shield systems typically absorb and then drain noise/RF energy to component ground, modulating and distorting the critical "reference" ground plane, which in turn causes a distortion of the signal. NDS\'s alternating layers of metal and carbon-loaded synthetics "shield the shield," absorbing and reflecting most of this noise/RF energy before it reaches the layer attached to ground.'] ['AudioQuest 1.5\xa0m Diamond USB A-B. Some lasers can produce light in an omnidirectional pattern to allow scanning of barcodes from different angles. Other barcode readers contain CCD (charge-coupled device) light sensors instead of a laser for accuracy and wear resistance. Barcode scanners with raster scanning, area imaging, and other scanning technologies can allow scanning of two-dimensional (2D) or Portable Document Format 417 (PDF417) barcodes, among other types. Some barcode readers provide onboard flash memory to allow the storage of barcode data before transmitting it to a computer or host system through a USB cable or wireless WLAN or Bluetooth connection. Many barcode readers have a handle for handheld use and come with a stand or a charging cradle for fixed position applications, while others are designed for stationary use on a counter or another flat surface. Garmin Vector 3 Pedal-Based Power Meter ["

Accurately measuring your power while cycling has never been simpler than with the new Garmin Vector 3 pedal-based power meter. Unlike previous versions of the Garmin Vector, the Vector 3 features a sleek, pod-less design for improved cornering clearance as well as simpler installation. No technical expertise is required for installation - all you need to know how to do is install pedals on your crankset. And since the power sensors are embedded in the pedals, bike-to-bike transfer is also incredibly easy as you just need to remove the pedals and install them on another bike. Other new features include the addition of Bluetooth connectivity to go along with the ANT+ connectivity so you'll have more options than ever regarding a compatible cycling computer of fitness device for data transmission and viewing. And it goes without saying that the Vector 3 pairs seamlessly with Garmin devices and apps for full integration into the Garmin cycling ecosystem.

Of course, the Garmin Vector 3 pedals continue to deliver reliable, accurate data on every training session. Unlike other power meters, the Vector 3 measures power at the pedal, where force is applied. With force sensors in each pedal you'll have the capacity to see right and left leg power independently. The Vector 3 provides data on total power, cadence, as well as advanced cycling dynamics to show how and where you're producing power and feature a battery life of up to 120 hours. The pedals themselves are lightweight at just 316 grams/pair and utilize tried and true LOOK Ko compatible cleats.
